  "text": "## Kafka Consumer Group Rebalance Protocol Implementation\n\nThis analysis identifies all Java source files in the Apache Kafka codebase under `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/` that define classes containing 'Rebalance' in the class name. These classes play critical roles in the consumer group rebalance protocol.\n\n### Rebalance Callback Handler Classes\n\n**ConsumerRebalanceListenerInvoker** (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489: clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ConsumerRebalanceListenerInvoker.java)\n- Role: Callback handler for the consumer rebalance protocol\n- Responsibility: Encapsulates invocation of ConsumerRebalanceListener callback methods (onPartitionsAssigned, onPartitionsRevoked, onPartitionsLost) when partition assignment changes\n- Key methods: invokePartitionsAssigned(), invokePartitionsRevoked(), invokePartitionsLost()\n\n**StreamsRebalanceListenerInvoker** (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489: clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/StreamsRebalanceListenerInvoker.java)\n- Role: Callback handler for the Kafka Streams rebalance protocol\n- Responsibility: Encapsulates invocation of StreamsRebalanceListener callback methods (onTasksRevoked, onTasksAssigned, onAllTasksLost) when task assignments change in Streams\n- Key methods: invokeTasksRevoked(), invokeTasksAssigned(), invokeAllTasksLost()\n\n### Rebalance Event Classes\n\n**ConsumerRebalanceListenerCallbackNeededEvent** (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489: clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/events/ConsumerRebalanceListenerCallbackNeededEvent.java)\n- Role: Background event signifying that a ConsumerRebalanceListener callback needs to be invoked\n- Responsibility: Communicates from network I/O thread to application thread that a rebalance callback is needed\n- Properties: Contains the method name and affected TopicPartitions\n\n**ConsumerRebalanceListenerCallbackCompletedEvent** (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489: clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/events/ConsumerRebalanceListenerCallbackCompletedEvent.java)\n- Role: Application event signifying that a ConsumerRebalanceListener callback has been executed\n- Responsibility: Notifies the network I/O thread that the application has completed executing a rebalance callback\n- Properties: Contains method name, completion future, and any errors that occurred\n\n### Rebalance Data Classes\n\n**StreamsRebalanceData** (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489: clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/StreamsRebalanceData.java)\n- Role: Data holder for Streams rebalance protocol participation\n- Responsibility: Contains all data needed for Kafka Streams to participate in the rebalance protocol\n- Components: TaskId, HostInfo, and Assignment classes for representing stream tasks and their assignments\n\n**StreamsRebalanceListener** (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489: clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/StreamsRebalanceListener.java)\n- Role: Listener interface for Streams rebalance events\n- Responsibility: Defines callback contract for handling task revocation, assignment, and loss events\n- Methods: onTasksRevoked(), onTasksAssigned(), onAllTasksLost()\n\n**ConsumerRebalanceListenerMethodName** (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489: clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ConsumerRebalanceListenerMethodName.java)\n- Role: Enumeration of ConsumerRebalanceListener callback method names\n- Responsibility: Provides static type-safe names for the three rebalance callback methods\n- Values: ON_PARTITIONS_REVOKED, ON_PARTITIONS_ASSIGNED, ON_PARTITIONS_LOST\n\n### Rebalance Metrics Manager Classes\n\n**RebalanceMetricsManager** (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489: clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/metrics/RebalanceMetricsManager.java)\n- Role: Abstract base class for rebalance metrics management\n- Responsibility: Defines the contract for recording rebalance start/end and tracking whether a rebalance is in progress\n- Key methods: recordRebalanceStarted(), recordRebalanceEnded(), rebalanceStarted(), maybeRecordRebalanceFailed()\n\n**ConsumerRebalanceMetricsManager** (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489: clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/metrics/ConsumerRebalanceMetricsManager.java)\n- Role: Coordinator - metrics manager for consumer group rebalances\n- Responsibility: Tracks and records rebalance latency, frequency, and failure metrics for the consumer protocol\n- Metrics: rebalance-latency-avg, rebalance-latency-max, rebalance-total, rebalance-rate-per-hour, failed-rebalance-total\n- Implementation: Extends RebalanceMetricsManager, uses sensor-based metrics aggregation\n\n**ShareRebalanceMetricsManager** (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489: clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/metrics/ShareRebalanceMetricsManager.java)\n- Role: Coordinator - metrics manager for share group rebalances\n- Responsibility: Tracks and records rebalance metrics specifically for the Kafka Share API consumer protocol\n- Metrics: rebalance-total, rebalance-rate-per-hour\n- Implementation: Extends RebalanceMetricsManager, simplified metrics for share protocol\n\n**RebalanceCallbackMetricsManager** (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489: clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/metrics/RebalanceCallbackMetricsManager.java)\n- Role: Callback handler metrics manager\n- Responsibility: Measures the latency and performance of rebalance listener callback invocations\n- Metrics: partition-revoked-latency (avg/max), partition-assigned-latency (avg/max), partition-lost-latency (avg/max)\n- Key methods: recordPartitionsRevokedLatency(), recordPartitionsAssignedLatency(), recordPartitionsLostLatency()\n\n## Summary\n\nThe rebalance protocol implementation in Kafka consists of 11 classes with 'Rebalance' in their names, organized into four functional categories:\n\n1. **Callback Handlers** (2 classes): ConsumerRebalanceListenerInvoker, StreamsRebalanceListenerInvoker\n2. **Events** (2 classes): ConsumerRebalanceListenerCallbackNeededEvent, ConsumerRebalanceListenerCallbackCompletedEvent  \n3. **Data/Interfaces** (3 classes): StreamsRebalanceData, StreamsRebalanceListener, ConsumerRebalanceListenerMethodName\n4. **Metrics** (4 classes): RebalanceMetricsManager, ConsumerRebalanceMetricsManager, ShareRebalanceMetricsManager, RebalanceCallbackMetricsManager\n\nThese classes work together to coordinate consumer group rebalancing, execute user callbacks, track rebalance metrics, and support both the classic consumer protocol and the newer Streams protocol."
